	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 12th 1:26 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.91]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings,<br><br>You are comparing apples to oranges...ie: 1-hs and 2-hs. Trying to compare the two is not the way to go about it.<br><br>I'm sure there are many strategies out there for deciding 1-hs vs 2-hs. Here's what I do.  If I am in a small group and the mob can be stunned, then I use my Sword of the Morning.  The stun is so nice that damage to the group can be significantly reduced, even if it only procs once during the battle.  <br><br>However, if I am in a larger group, a raid setting, or the mob is not stunnable (ie: Giant's, etc.) then I usually go to my 2-hs because of the damage. The only exception to this is when I am the Main Tank. When main tanking or pulling, I use 1-hs. I can build more aggro with 1-hs and can also Bash the mob when I pull it to give me that extra step on my way back to the group.<br><br>While the Sword of the Morning does very nice damage, it's the Proc that makes it extra special, IMO.  If the proc isn't being beneficial to the group, go with something else. That would be my advice.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
