	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok heres what to do in my opinion. As far as armor goes, you need to get out of bronze and such, either A) quest for your armor of ro, or B) gain another 2 levels and start getting into Plane of Fear raids to get some Valorium. As far as your weapons, I dont know what the stats of the MotQ is but I'd go for possibly an Arbitors Combine Greatsword at your level. Its a pretty nice sword, and I'm sure its a little better since the patch. As far as your priorities, AC and STR and HP should be your utmost concerns in my opinion. Resists are good yes, but get resist gear that you swap out sometimes when needed, dont make it your main equip unless its a really good item that ties resists in with good equip. And definately when you hit 50, start trying to work on your Fiery Avenger...it may seem out of reach but if you dont try, then of course it is. And beyond that is Fiery Defender, I love this sword cause it has every stat bonus you could want, great damage, ac, and you can bash with it. Its a long hard road to get that sword, but it can be done, so dont count yourself out =). Keep up the good work young knight.<br><br>--<br>Trevekk Valor<br>Epic Knight of Mithaniel Marr<br>Beloved of Kaniel<br>Ilsik Haucil<br>--<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
