	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello all!<br><br>I recently started a paladin on the Morrell-Thule server, and have been fortunate to meet some very generous high level characters who have given me some nice things for my level.  I am only level 4 at this point, and my base strength is 95 (human).<br><br>Most of it is leather with some banded, but there are two decisions I need to make about what to wear:<br><br>1)Bronze collar (AC 6, Wt 5.0) or studded leather gorget (AC 3, Wt 0.5, Str+1, Sta+1)<br><br>2)When I hit 6 and get bash, I have two shields to choose from, a round shield (AC 5, Wt 5.0) or a large wooden kite shield (AC 7, Wt 12.5!!).<br><br>My problem is that with a base strength of 95 and base agility of 75, it's kind of a battle between getting a higher armor class and being encumbered all the time (reducing agility and thus AC), or using lower AC stuff and being able to carry more.<br><br>I know I'm still at a pretty low level where this is not going to be much of an issue, I may just bank the heavier gear until later.  So I guess my question is, are strength enhancing items going to be a necessity if I ever want to wear better armor?  If so, what should I look for and when should I start looking for it?<br><br>Thanks in advance for any advice...<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
