	   <tr><td colspan=2>sdenchfi,<br><br>I see you are a Dwarven Paladin. Yes, it just so happens I can recommend a GREAT 1-handed weapon, but it is not Slashing! As a dwarf you get the privilege to wield a great 1-hand BLUNT weapon called a Dwarven Sap: 8 damage/20 delay. It's down right speedy and I would recommend you pick on up when you can garner enough cash. They sell for a variety of prices but I have seen them for as low as 100 plat.  Just something to keep your eyes open for.  <br><br>I have long been a proponent of practicing 1-hand blunt, as well as ALL your other skills. Here's a little story for you. I was recently awarded a Club of the Ice Ocean (kinda like a Sap on Steroids!) that drops from Lodizal.  It is 14 damage, 27 delay, +10 hps, +3 strength and procs Frost Strike which is a 149 pt DD. It is a sweet club and the Raid Leader told me, in no uncertain terms, that the reason I got the club instead of two of the warriors (who really love to dual wield it) was because my 1-hb was over 200!! He was SO surprised to see that that he awarded the club to me for helping kill Lodizal.  So all my training paid off!  I now use the club regularly, along with my Sword of the Morning for 1-hs.<br><br>As for other 1-hs weapons that you can obtain at level 20, Ghoulbane is the first one that comes to mind. A very nice weapon.  When I was your level I didn't use 1-hs much, so I can't be more help. Perhaps someone else can pitch in with some 1-hs information??<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Paladin<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
