	   <tr><td colspan=2>Re: Ro armor not worth the effort.<br><br>This is one of my ongoing complaints about EQ in general.  Look at the quest list and you will find perhaps five that are worth your time.  <br><br>A big problem with these quests is that they are out of date.  Another problem is the EQ economy.  A BABS can be had for 350p.  I had one by lvl 21 but would I ever think to try and *hunt* for one?  No way.  Call me in about 20 levels.  The trickle down effect has certainly been a factor.  <br><br>This has created the cycle you're talking about of just killing stuff to make money to buy better stuff instead of trying to get it yourself.  This has further reduced the challenge.  Why get a good, solid group together to try and tackle that tough dungeon for that rare item when you can camp an easy room for a day and then just buy it?  <br><br>On the upside, I've heard that Luclin will introduce a method to sell that doesn't require you to be present.  I.e. you set your price with a NPC or something and then head off.  It's about time.  I know a lot of people that drop their prices because they are simply tired of auctioning a 200p item for five days straight.  I think this should help with the problem, assuming it is implemented effectively.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
