	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Fellow Paladins,<br><br>I have now been successful in obtaining BOTH the Frost book and the Burnt book for the Book of Scale!  WOOOT ME!!  :) (By the way, I got my Frost Book from Gorenaire in DL and my Burnt Book from Severilous in EJ&#8230;so it IS possible to get your books without Naggy or Vox!)  Needless to say, once I got the two book-halves, things have moved along rather quickly.<br><br>I have completed combining both book halves with the reasonably new quest NPC gal outside of Qeynos to actually make the Book of Scale.  She is left of the gate to Qeynos by some boxes.   I&#8217;m glad I didn&#8217;t have to go to the Blind Fish Bar inside Neriak. They hate me in Neriak&#8230;I just never could pass up those free Bronze Longswords the Guards always gave me!  :)<br><br>I have turned the Book of Scale into the Oracle in OOT and received the Soul of Miragul.  The Oracle conned Indifferent to me when I did this turn in.<br><br>I have turned in the Soul from the Oracle to Lich Miragul in the Everfrost Caves and killed the REAL Lich Miragul when he spawned.  (Just a word of Warning&#8230;upon spawning, he IMMEDIATELY hit me with a 1500-pt Life Tap so be ready for that&#8230;thankfully he only did this once!)  I looted his head and the Robe. I took approximately 20 people in their 50&#8217;s, including 2 lvl 60 warriors. He dropped easily but not immediately.<br><br>I already have my Soulfire and my Ghoulbane, of course, so I am ready for the Turn-in in the Plane of Air to get the mini-epic Fiery Avenger. <br><br>I have looted my Tainted Breastplate in the Plane of Hate and got my Crystal from Jark in Kaladim. I have turned this in to the Reklon Gnallen (?) in Erudin and he gave me the Shining Breastplate.   (As a note&#8230;I did this turn-in to Reklon with INDIFFERENT Faction.  I had heard that you must be at least Warmly with the Deepwater Knights to do this and that is just not true. I am living proof as of last night.)<br><br>So, this brings me to my next few steps and I was looking for some input on the following questions:<br><br>1) How often does Kirak Vil spawn in Nektulos and where can I find him for the Tainted Shield?<br>2) Once I do find him&#8230;how hard is he to take down? I have read the posts on this site, Everlore, Illias Bestiary, etc. but there are many differing stories. He hits for 180, no he hits for 100, no he is completely MR, no he Regens quickly so you have to DOT him with Shaman, Druid and Necro spells to combat against the Regen, One group can do it, No 2 groups are minimum, He wiped out my two groups...etc.  Anyone who has actually DONE it, I would appreciate your input&#8230;Praetor????<br>3) What is the ACTUAL Faction Requirement to do the Turn-in in the Plane of Air for the Fiery Avenger? I'm tired of killing poor Elial Brook for DW Knight faction! <br>4) What is the ACTUAL Faction Requirement to do the Turn-in in the Plane of Fear for the Fiery Defender?  I am tired of killing poor Elial Brook for DW Knight faction!<br><br>I am not concerned about the Keeper of Tombs in The Hole. I assume he is a straight forward opponent that drops the Tainted Sword once defeated.<br><br>I am moving along quickly and can actually SMELL my Epic Weapon which is driving me onward. If ANYONE has some factual information (not rumor, or I once read, or my friend&#8217;s buddy&#8217;s brother did it&#8230;) I&#8217;d love to hear it.<br><br>Once I get past the Turn-in in the Plane of Air, at least I am past the Catastrophic Failure stage and can repeat the Tainted Shield, Tainted Sword parts of the Fiery Defender quest if I should fail on one of them.<br><br>Thanks and looking forward to your posts!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>&#8220;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&#8221;<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
