	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 6th 4:04 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>By far the least used class I've seen is Bard.  I think people just think musician = weak.  The first time I even even grouped with a bard was in the warrens around level 20.  He knew the area well and led us to some of the decent content.  Mid-fight he breaks out his guitar and he's singing tunes... what the hell?  But then I started getting buffed out of the wazoo.  Funky buffs I'd never seen before with wierd durations.  <br><br>Given the different style of play and the general ignorance of their abilities Bards are often ignored in the mid-level game I've noticed.  They are definately a group class but most groups don't know how to use them.  One bard I ran into set up THREE socials (about 15 lines of text) to explain what he was going to do in our group as far as buffing and fighting (basically explaining what his group role would be).  He had to explain this stuff on such a regular basis he just created a script for every group he ran into.  Makes sense.  <br><br>The other class I don't see much is monks.  Don't know why, but I just don't.  <br><br>On a sidenote, the least used race I've ever seen is troll and I have only seen one female troll in the time I've been playing EQ (they ooogly).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
