<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100507472542022></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100507472542022><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100507472542022>RE: Off Topic</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100507472542022#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=600><span id=Guru>PraetorFenix</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>238 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 6th 2:25 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.34]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would have to say shamans and bards are the least common characters I see at the end game.  I would say primarly due to the difficulty in playing them at high levels and the boredom associated with a lot of their tasks.<br><br>Shamans are restricted to primarily debuffing and buffing on raids, and bards are generally regarded as mana batteries.  Why?  Not because that's all they do, but that's all people THINK they can do.  They have lots of abilities that are rarely realized to their full potential due to the taxing restrictions placed on them by the sometimes overwhelming tasks they are assigned.<br><br>Personally I like to shuffle bards around between different kinds of groups to add a bit of variety.  Sometimes I have them do the mana battery thing, sometimes I have them whip up a huge damage shield in a main tank group, and sometimes I have them augment rogue and monk groups with massive atk buffs.<br><br>Shamans however are a different story.  With it being necessary to cast malo on near everything we fight in ToV, then slow it, then cast Focus and stamina on everybody, then Avatar the main tank, do poison and disease resist when called for, and possibly backup heal with Torpor...  Their job is often very stressful and tedious.  However it's nice to be needed for everything we do.  Not a single other class can cast focus or stamina, or Malo and Turgur like they do.  Magicians and enchanters together come close with Mala and Forlorn Deeds, but neither can match the debuffing and slow power of a single shaman.<br><br>Well.  That was a bit of a rant.  So if you want to be unique, be a human bard or a troll shaman.  Those are the least played races for that particular class.<br>&nbsp;<br><b>Praetor</b>, 60th Crusader<br>Avatars of Discord</td></tr>
