<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100500981321404></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100500981321404><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100500981321404>RE: Easy?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100500981321404#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83710><span id=Sage>jcasetnl</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>113 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 5th 8:23 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I like playing a paladin mainly for the low downtime.  Although paladin heals aren't ussually useful during a fight they are great afterwards for getting right back into it.  A few of the spells are useful in battle but paladin 'nukes' are some of the weekest in the game.  <br><br>Another thing about pallys is that they are ussually the last ones standing in a fight that has gone bad.  If your group gets overrun and everyone is heading for the door with one bubble of health left your lay of hands almost guarantees you will make it out.  Once outside you heal up and head back in while everyone else is at least a half hour behind you due to corpse runs and regaining lost exp.  <br><br>All of this moot to stupid players.  You really have to think when playing a pally.  There aren't many simple fear/kite routines pallys can employ.  <br><br>Your spells will always lag behind a cleric and are there to augment your melee or reduce downtime.  I have rarely seen a cleric use his or her spells as well as a pally in combat.  Even simple things such as rooting a mob when they are low on mana in order to get some med time seems lost on them.  <br><br>Lastly, pallys are one of the few classes that can group purely.  In other words, three pallys grouped together are very strong.  You don't need a melee/cast/heal combination in most cases.  We can take the damage, control agro well, root, step back and heal and jump right back in the fight.  As always, even if overrun we can pull out the LOH as a last resort and get out of there.  <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
